tweet: @c_ridgway Same experience man. Floods of thoughts and memories, hung on visual hooks.

name: Dave 🌊
tweet: It also helps us share a common history, as we move through our days we all contribute to a collective record keeping of what life looks like in our time. What draws you to this practice and why do you like seeing images made by others?

name: Dave 🌊
tweet: It also teaches me lessons about the systems of the world- lessons that apply to many other areas of my life. I love that so many more people have access to the experience of photography because I think it makes life more interesting and more fun.

name: Dave 🌊
tweet: What is it that you like about photography? For me, every image is a catalyst for a cascade of memories, an emotional stimulant, a cross-section of time itself. Making photographs keeps me observant, and allows me to experience my environment more deeply.
